sidebyside.p:
We substitute x=\alert{-1} into the equation for the circle, and solve for y.
\begin{aligned}[t] (\alert{-1}^2)+y^2 \amp = 4\\ y^2 \amp = 4-1 = 3\\ y \amp = \pm \sqrt{3}\\ \end{aligned}
The points are (-1, \sqrt{3}) and (-1,\sqrt{3}), as shown at right. Note that \sqrt{3} \approx 1.732.

