sidebyside.p:
The radius of the pie is 4 inches, so its circumference is 2\pi (4) inches. A 60° wedge, shown at right, is 
    \dfrac{1}{6} of the entire pie, so its edge is \dfrac{1}{6} of the circumference.  The exact length of the arc is thus 
 \dfrac{1}{6} (8\pi)=\dfrac{4\pi}{3} \text{ inches.}

